<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON VIEW: A BIRTHDAY THAT TAKES THE CAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY LOU LOPER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Those 500th anniversaries are rare. Try to outdo Christopher Columbus. His 
quincentenary will be the topic at a reception Thursday at the Dorothy Chandler 
Pavilion of the Music Center. Talk will focus on the international tall ship 
Parade of Sail that will escort the three Columbus replica caravels -- the 
Nina, Pinta and Santa Maria -- into the Port of Long Beach on Sept. 27, 1992. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles County Supervisors Peter F. Schabarum, Kenneth Hahn, Edmund D. 
Edelman, Deane Dana and Michael D. Antonovich host the kickoff here with 
AT&amp;T. Guest of honor will be John N. Goudie, chairman of the U. S. 
Christopher Columbus Quincentenary Jubilee Commission. County chief of protocol 
Sandra Ausman has the happy job of coordinating. 
</P>
<P>
PAST PERFECT: Kathleen and Tom McCarthy's black-tie celebration at Los Angeles 
Country Club with Wayne Foster's orchestra attracting guests to the dance floor 
in droves. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Mary Jensen and Joni and Clark Smith's "Latin Casual Brazilian Beat" for the 
affianced Ashley Brittingham and Jeff McDermott at the Beach Club with lessons 
for all in the nuances of the lambada. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Norma and David McIntyre's 25th wedding anniversary black-tie party for 200 at 
the Bistro Garden at Coldwater. . . . 
</P>
<P>
The engagement party -- a biking soiree from the Beach Club to Venice's 72 
Market Street -- honoring Kevin McKenzie and Erin Evans. It was hosted by Sally 
and Joe Keon, Donna and Michael Mellentin, Dennis and Linda Vaughn and George 
and Jane Barrett. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Dorothy Shea's divine luncheon at the California Club feting bride-to-be Hilary 
Weber. . . . Carol Inman's tea feting her future daughter-in-law Lori Bjorseth. 
</P>
<P>
STARS: Veteran volunteer Julia Dockweiler, whose name is synonymous with Los 
Angeles history, got the Spirit of Voluntarism Award at the Junior League of 
Los Angeles meeting at the Los Angeles Athletic Club this week. Jan Kern takes 
over the presidency from Robin Patterson Nenninger. 
</P>
<P>
Sandy Duncan and Henry Winkler, in the angels' spot for Center Theatre Group 
Volunteers "Angels' Night" memorabilia auction. It benefits the Mark Taper 
Forum's Improvisational Theatre Project. Shirley Colby and Gail Newman 
co-chaired. . . . 
</P>
