<HEADLINE>
<P>
FLASH FROM THE PAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Temple City, celebrating its 30th anniversary of incorporation, was founded by 
Walter P. Temple in 1922. In 1936, the Town of Temple was officially designated 
a city by the U.S. Postal Service. A successful incorporation election in May, 
1960, made its city status official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
