142 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUNGALOW HEAVEN NEIGHBORHOOD TOURS PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PASADENA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Bungalow Heaven Neighborhood Assn. will sponsor its first walking tour of 
homes in the historic Bungalow Heaven Landmark District on June 3, from 10 a.m. 
to 4 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
A neighborhood of more than 800 homes, Bungalow Heaven has a large 
concentration of California and Craftsman bungalows. The 12 homes on the tour, 
dating to the early 20th Century, were selected because of their unusual and 
varied architectural styles. 
</P>
<P>
Many will display furniture and decorative arts of the period. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets for the tour cost $10 for adults and children between 5 and 12; $7 for 
Bungalow Heaven Neighborhood Assn. members, and $5 for senior citizens. For 
advance tickets, call (818) 798-5200. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets will also be available on the day of the event at McDonald Park, at the 
intersection of East Mountain Street and North Wilson Avenue in Bungalow 
Heaven. 
</P>
</TEXT>
