<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARCHITECTURAL HERITAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kaplan's column ("Preservation Lesson: UCLA Flunks Test," May 13) discusses how 
ironic it is that UCLA, whose library houses the Richard Neutra Archives, is 
planning to destroy the UES buildings designed by Richard Neutra. 
</P>
<P>
The loss of our architectural heritage is also an embarrassing one give that 
Richard Neutra is the only Southern California architect to have won the 
American Institute of Architects' Gold Medal award. 
</P>
<P>
BEN ANDRADE 
</P>
<P>
Silverlake 
</P>
</TEXT>
