<DATE>
<P>
May 27, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Travel; Part L; Page 20; Column 2; Travel Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
96 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
THANKS FOR TIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have been meaning to write and thank Jerry Hulse for a squib in his Travel 
Tips column last year on CampAlaska Tours, P.O. Box 872247, Wasilla, Alaska 
99687, phone (907) 376-9438. 
</P>
<P>
I went with them for two weeks and had about the best time I have ever had on a 
vacation. We must have covered 2,000 miles and saw just about everything. It 
was a most reasonably priced trip, and the people in our group, from all over 
the world, were bright, fun and good sports. I highly recommend this company 
for a great way to really experience Alaska. 
</P>
<P>
VAUGHN HART 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
