<HEADLINE>
<P>
A POEM TO SEE BY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I read Vikram Seth's poem, "All You Who Sleep Tonight," to my sightless one. 
</P>
<P>
I read it last. 
</P>
<P>
After a silence, she said, "And you were not afraid to read that to me. Thank 
you. Good night, my friend." 
</P>
<P>
My thanks to you. 
</P>
<P>
FRED SCIFERS 
</P>
<P>
DOWNEY 
</P>
<P>
 Scifers is a volunteer reader for a blind woman. The poem he refers to is 
reprinted below: 
</P>
<P>
 All you who sleep tonight 
</P>
<P>
 Far from the ones you love 
</P>
<P>
 No hand to left or right, 
</P>
<P>
 And emptiness above -- 
</P>
<P>
 Know that you aren't alone, 
</P>
<P>
 The whole world shares your tears, 
</P>
<P>
 some for two nights or one, 
</P>
<P>
 And some for all their years. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
