<HEADLINE>
<P>
GREAVES NAMED TO CAL STATE L.B. BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONG BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Roger F. Greaves, president and chief executive officer of Health Net, has been 
named a founding member of the board of governors of the Cal State Long Beach 
Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
Greaves, an alumnus, is chairman of the university's Annual Fund campaign. 
</P>
<P>
University President Curtis McCray said the board will be "involved in helping 
to determine the future direction of the university physically, academically 
and financially." 
</P>
<P>
Other founding members of include Wayne Armstrong, president and chief 
executive officer of Del Taco; Norman Coulson, president and chief executive 
officer of Glendale Federal Savings &amp; Loan Assn., and Peter Ridder, 
publisher of the Long Beach Press-Telegram. 
</P>
<P>
The board held its first meeting April 30. 
</P>
