<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SIMI VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
PLANNERS ENDORSE 3 HOUSING PROJECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAREN McKEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Simi Valley Planning Commission has recommended that the City Council 
approve three housing projects that would add nearly 600 homes to the city. 
</P>
<P>
Commission members approved two large projects proposed by Milner Development 
Co. and VTN West Inc. 
</P>
<P>
Milner Development is proposing 237 single-family houses on 62 acres near 
Tierra Rejada and Madera roads. VTN West is proposing 350 single-family houses 
on a 277-acre parcel south of the Arroyo Simi and Royal Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
The commission also recommended approval of a request by Fred Madjar to divide 
a 2.73-acre lot into 11 single-family lots on the south side of Presidio Drive 
near Lathrop Avenue. KAREN McKEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<CORRECTION-DATE>
<P>
May 30, 1990, Wednesday, Ventura County Edition 
</P>
</CORRECTION-DATE>
<CORRECTION>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
<P>
No action -- An article published Sunday in The Times incorrectly reported that 
the Simi Valley Planning Commission had approved two large housing projects 
proposed by Milner Development Co. and VTN West. The commission took no action 
on the projects. 
</P>
</CORRECTION>
