<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: CHATSWORTH CYCLIST 66TH IN TOUR OF ITALY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John Tomac of Chatsworth moved into 66th place in cycling's Tour of Italy on 
Saturday after a 42nd-place finish in the mountainous La Spezia-to-Langhirano 
stage. 
</P>
<P>
Tomac completed the 109.12 miles in 5 hours 9 minutes 47 seconds, 5:32 behind 
winner Vladimir Poulnikov of the Soviet Union. 
</P>
<P>
Tomac, who entered Saturday's stage 95th, trails leader Gianni Bugno of Italy 
by 34:30. 
</P>
<P>
Tomac remains the top U. S. rider in a field that also includes reigning Tour 
de France champion Greg LeMond. 
</P>
<P>
LeMond, plagued by injury and illness throughout this season, is 133rd, 1:21:40 
behind Bugno. 
</P>
<P>
Marianne Spencer, Betsy Lund and Heather Clark of Antelope Valley College were 
named to the All-Foothill Conference softball team, as chosen by coaches. 
</P>
<P>
Spencer, a pitcher, was 7-5 with a 2.57 earned-run average. Lund, an infielder, 
batted .339 with 15 runs batted in and Clark, an outfielder, batted .359. 
</P>
<P>
Cheri Bainbridge and Pam Craycraft, also of Antelope Valley, were named to the 
all-conference second team. 
</P>
