<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHROEDER VICTOR IN THREE-QUARTER MIDGET MAIN RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL OLSON, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gary Schroeder of Burbank edged Page Jones of Rolling Hills to win the 20-lap 
United States Auto Club Western States Series Three-Quarter Midget main event 
before 2,225 at Ventura Raceway on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
Schroeder had just enough power to get past leader Jones, the son of 1960 
Indianapolis 500 winner Parnelli Jones, on the front straightaway on Lap 8 and 
held on to nip Jones by two car lengths. 
</P>
<P>
Jay Drake of Valencia took third. 
</P>
<P>
The victory also moved Schroeder into a tie with Ricky Gray for the most USAC 
main event career wins at 12. 
</P>
<P>
Sleepy Tripp of Costa Mesa won the 30-lap USAC Midget main event. 
</P>
<P>
Midget 10-lap heat race winners were Robby Flock of the City of Industry, 
Tripp, Hank Butcher of San Leandro, and Gary Howard of Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
Flock's 10-lap heat race victory took only 2 minutes 10 seconds, breaking the 
Midget 10-lap record time on the one-quarter-mile dirt oval of 2 minutes 17 
seconds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
