<P>
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Cost to Employers 
</P>
<P>
By a vote of 187 to 213, the House rejected an amendment to limit the cost to 
businesses of accommodating disabled workers under the Americans With 
Disabilities Act (above). The cost of providing for a handicapped employee was 
to have been capped at 10% of the pay for the job in question. 
</P>
<P>
Supporter Bill McCollum (R-Fla.) said, "This is the small-business amendment in 
this legislation." 
</P>
<P>
Opponent Bruce A. Morrison (D-Conn.) said, "Arbitrary formula limits are not 
what this legislation is about." 
</P>
<P>
A yes vote was to cap the bill's cost to employers. 
</P>
