<HEADLINE>
<P>
LUKAS' STELLA MADRID WINS THE ACORN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wayne Lukas-trained Stella Madrid led all the way, winning the $174,300 Acorn 
Stakes for 3-year-old fillies by 1 1/2 lengths Saturday at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
The victory was the second in a row in the Acorn for Lukas, who last year 
saddled 3-year-old filly champion Open Mind to victory in the race, the first 
in New York's filly Triple Tiara series. 
</P>
</TEXT>
